Caesar Cipher Encryption

Overview
⇒ This project is a program for encrypting and decrypting text using the Caesar cipher method. The program operates through the console, accepting command-line parameters (args). The entire process of encryption, decryption, and other operations is performed using files.

Features

Argument Handling
⇒ The project supports command-line argument passing, ensuring flexibility in usage.

Encryption and Decryption
⇒ Implemented functions for encrypting and decrypting data to ensure secure transmission and storage of information.

Brute Force
⇒ The project includes a brute-force key enumeration, attempting all possible keys.

File System Operations
⇒ The program supports file system operations, providing convenient interaction with data.
